			<div class="blogComment">
				<a name="109580929174595467"></a> 
				Thanks for your question, Phil.&nbsp; I have responded in a new entry, "<A HREF="http://www.blogger.com/r?http%3A%2F%2Fnfocentrale.net%2Forcmid%2Fblog%2F2004%2F09%2Feducation-what-does-student-centric.asp">Education: What Does Student-Centric Look Like?</A>"&nbsp; I would love to know what you see that could have a student-centric feel in your on-the-ground courses.&nbsp; Are you able to set up communication and electronic discussion between the physical class meetings?&nbsp; One reason for my being in this program is so that I can qualify myself as an on-the-ground lecturer!&nbsp; I would like to participate in on-line delivery too, but I think being directly with students has its own quality and I want to contribute that way too.<br />
